tweet: What advice would Dan give to people new to cannabis? ‚ÄúThe best advice I can give is to educate yourself about cannabis. If you look at the history of cannabis, it was approved in 1851 to be included in the US Pharmacopeia. Look at cannabis as another type of medication.‚Äù (5/5)

name: Acreage Holdings
tweet: ‚ÄúMy son who is 14 also has epilepsy but manifests differently. Cannabis has saved their lives & given them better control of their epilepsy. When the MMJ law passed in NY I knew I wanted to work with sick patients and use cannabis in conjunction with their medical regimen.‚Äù (4/5)

name: Acreage Holdings
tweet: When asked why he works in cannabis, Dan said, ‚ÄúI have 2 children who are disabled and have numerous medical complexities. For 20 years my daughter has suffered with uncontrolled epilepsy. Hospitalizations, medical procedures, & medications have not been enough to help.‚Äù (3/5)

name: Acreage Holdings
tweet: ‚ÄúAs a medical practitioner, the intense situations we dealt with change the way you view patients and life,‚Äù says Dan. ‚ÄúI have grown to be a more empathetic person and want to be a person who makes change for the better.‚Äù (2/5)
